\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid9461452 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Your name's Mrs. Sharp,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Can you tell me when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 September 13th - 1894. 1894.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Glaister's Cottage, Kirkgunzeon. Glaister's Cottage, Kirkgunzeion, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 You told me that's not the house that your mother lived in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 No, it was - we were living in Drumnail then, Drumnail Kilgunzeon,
 you see, Glaister's Cottage, he - he was the shep - was the farmers - Glaister's was the famer's house, and - and my father was the shepherd, and - and the sheperd's house was Drumnail you see; Drumnail Kirkgunzeon. I think that's all changed now of cour
se.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Your mother only went to Glaister's cottage for you being born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Yes. Yes, we were up there - up there for - 'til she was all right with her - her - a Mrs. - Bowes - Boyes, Boyes or something they called her, a lady - she just stayed - for the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Was this usual for people to go away to have a baby like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Well, I think in - in the old times it was - there werenae any maternity hospitals in Dumfries you see, there were no word of the - had the hospitals in Dumfries then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Your mother didn't have any relations round about that could come and help her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
No. No, she - there was the - there's the sun coming out - there were - mother brought up two boys - her - her sister's and my father's - belonged to a sister of my father'
s you see. Well, they - they were left - they were left for to - help a wee bit in the house, while my father was out at the hills you see. Big heather hills they were. The hea - heather - in the hills.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Did he have a lot of sheep to look after?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Had a lot of sheep to look after. Aye. And then - and then of course the - there in Drumnail - we could have - you had plenty out houses, and you kept pigs, and hens and - and - all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 For your own use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Aye, that was right - use, you had quite a good comfortable living. There.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Where did your father come from originally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Kirkmahoe. Kirkmahoe I think he - he was - he - the Swan's was born, there, I think he be born at Kirkmahoe I'm sure you see, but he lived - he lived at - at T
inwald too, near Tinwald you know like the - at the side of Tinwald - where - where his - his father and mother was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Was he a shepherd all the time, did he start off when he was a youngster being a shepherd?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 No. I think in his young days he was 
a groom, with - with the - with the - with the McCloughs you know the - the - aye - the - they - there - and there was a brother and him, you know - were together and that was the days of the coachmen, you know, they - they had liveries you see to put on,
 and they had to drive out the young Lords and tend to their horses and - and - and all that, that was the old old Buccleuchs. Where used - he used to tell us all about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 He'd tell you stories about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Ah. Aye. We used - we used to like to hear him telling us about his young days. When he was out driving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Great big coaches were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Yes. The - so he - he used to speak - and it was round about - a lot a - and he used to drive - he went for big long drives with them out too you know
, the - the coachman and - and one was the coachman, one was the footman you see, but they were in liveries - to the - he used to drive round about the - you know, the districts they had. Aye. The districts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 And then he went to be a shepherd after that did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Well - when - I think when he - when he married like - when - he - he - when he should - he would be a shepherd, he would start sheep - he - he - he was a young shepherd like for - to start with like you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Like an apprentice?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Aye, like an - apprentice, he would - he'd be like what you calls a - a - a single - then be like a - a married shepherd and then he would be like a single shepherd, and - and af - and after that he - he got married himself you see. And then he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 He would be looking for a job with a house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Yes. He got a - he got a house you see then, and - in a - in a - I think it was - I think it was Berwick - Berwick I think the - the name of the - the gentleman - that - that - that got him the - this job
 you see, the name of the shepherd and - and - and mother - and my mother - was - my mother was a laundry - laundress here, in - in the big house you see, my mother like, she - and - and he was - a young - he was young shepherd you see - at this - at this
 farm, and I think Berwick was the name of his - mas - master you see. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 So that's how they met?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
How they met you see and then they got married, and - and - it was - he was quite - they were - quite near to each other like, I mean to say they \endash 
 Mr. Berwick and the - the - the man - the Burn of Thornhill I think he was in the end, the - oh they were well to do gentlemen then you know the Berwicks. And Mrs. Berwick, and she had two daughters. She had two daughters too, and - and when we were - we
 used to get away - they used to come for us and take us away over and - and - for the day to play with daughters you know, Rosie and Jessie. Ro - Rosie and Jessie was the name of the daughters. And - and - and it was fun. And - and they enjoyed it, they 
enjoyed it you see, 'cos they had - we - we played about with them and - and I can remember the - them putting us on swings you know, giving us swings you see outside and that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 You got on quite well with the girls there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Yes, we got on fine with
 them. And - and you got lots of - of good clothes from them too you know, when they - when they grew out of their clothes - we come in for them. Very good, very kind. They were often good to mother and that - mother was a long time with - with them, and 
- she did a lot of the laundry work you know, the - the - doing up of the shirts and his collars and all like that for - so they - they - she did - was miss her terribly but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 So she carried on working after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Yes, she - aye, she -
 she - if she was near - if she was near she used to go - in to help them in the laundry you see. And she enjoyed it quite - well they were good to her. They were good to her, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Where did your mother come from originally?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Ruthwell I think. I
 think - Ruthwell. I think it was down that - way, where - ay, yes, down that way, Ruthwell. Her mother lived a long time down there, at Ruthwell and that way. But the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 With her father too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 No, her father was a shepherd - too, but he died - he 
died - an early age, with - with poisoning, he - he got at the dipper, you know, when they were dipping the sheep. There was something - he had - something about it, he used to hurt his knee or something, and he - he - this - this poison stuff, he got -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 It must have got into the wound?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Aye. Well it went through his system. Because he was - he died quite a - I think he - I think it did - it would be in his late fifties maybe when he was taken away, we used to hear mother speaking about him, becaus
e I never mind him, my grandfather like and that, and that grandfather, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 You remember your grannies though do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Yes, I'm called for her, I was called for her, aye. Alison Lockett. Alison Lockett you see Swan. Swan. Swan's my maiden name. S
o - I was - I was called for the - and - and - and often went to - went - when - when she was a widow - you see - she - she went - she went along to - there was a cousin - it was a cousin like of mother's at - Comlongan Castle, like - Comlongon Castle wit
h
 the - that would be the Johnson Douglas's place. They - this was the - the dairy part of this, this was the dairy part that he had, the big dairy part. It's where they - they used to get her over - and - and she got lots of milk back with her and all wit
h
 - when she was living alone, when she was living by herself. I'd often go to her. To stay. She was - she was - well she lived in the end, she lived to about nearly ninety, grandmother, my grandmother. And she was a - she was big strong looking woman, tal
l - and - she'd worked hard in her young days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Did your mother live to a good age too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Aye. Aye, she was nearly eighty - nearly eighty when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 When did she die, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 She died - in - well she - she was staying with m
e when she died, she - she - see my husband was - one of the policemen you see, and then you had the police houses at Marchmount, we - we'd one of the police houses there, and - and - she - she flitted there with us you see because I was looking after her
 
before that you see. And - and she - so she died there with us and it was 1940. 1940 was the year anyway, and - I can't now just quite remember whether it was - whether it was - March - March or anything. But I know that it - it - it was a big funeral she
 had.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 You were saying your father didn't have very good health?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
No, and I - he had - he was - he was a shepherd and had to move around - you see, you see, after we got out - out of Kirkgunzeon - and out - out around that way - he - he took a - a
 - a place - like it was - at - Crochmore, you see, Crochmore, he really - flitted out to Crochmore - and - the - he - he had - he'd quite a good - he - he'd quite a way of doing but he thought there were too many voices, you know there were - there was l
i
ke two different masters you know, and - and - it was difficult, so they - it was - and - and - Ferguson was the name of the - at - at the head one that had Crochmore then - then. It's a bachelor now I think isn't it, at Crochmore? But I think it is, but 
however, we - we went - we went to Shawhead school for a year, my sister and I. And the boys. The boys see too 'til they grew up you see, to - to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 The boys were both older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Aye, they - they - the ones that mother brought up from a - aye
, they were older, but - when they - when they went away - when - when they - I left the school, they - they sort of worked about - one was - were only about a year, managed a year at Crochmore because it was - nearer - my father had rheumatic fever and -
 and wasna very much good after that for a while you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Did that affect his heart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
It suddenly - it must have kind of weakened him or something, but - however - he would - he got the - applied for this - what it was called, Lochur, Noniaive, Lo
chur, a big farm it was, a big farm, but - but - it was - he was - it was a good place to be in too you see - and he got - got helps with - with his shepherding, he had - he got one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 He didn't have all the work to do himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 A young shepherd t
o help him and - and - both in the lambing season, and - and in - and the - you know - had lots of things you did - they - that he could do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 He'd be busy when they clipping as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Aye, clipping, aye, clipping up and all afterwards - ca
tch up all the handlings and all that, running about and he used to come - and - and - it was like a - a - he finished up with a - like a spree, as you called them, entertainments. Because you had a lot of shepherds you know gathered, and then there was -
 some of them players, with a violin and some of them singers and - suchlike as that and then they - they danced.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 After the work was done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Aye, on a flag floor. On a flag - yes, just flag floors and that. Enjoyed our - this was after the - the c
lipping was done you see. And - and they - they had a good - they had a good - meal that night too, and - they quite enjoyed sitting round about. Of course we were just - my sister and I see were just - had our hair, you know long and hanging down our sho
u
lders, you know, the - then, you know, and - and - and you - enjoyed watching them you see, and that. Oh it was good. It was good. We enjoyed it. And then - you see, the - there was like - you had like - two - there were two masters too at that really - C
a
lender - Stubbs and Callender, was the name of them you see for the first lot you see, and they had their - their - their - friends - came it was a good big house you see, and they - they came - they came - to stay - with them for a - for a bit. And - and
 - well - mother - mother helped them as much as she could too you see doing things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 In the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Aye. Because she was a good baker and - and that, but there were - the - they brought - they brought - some of their - sometimes they brought the -
 their - their own - their own needs and that you see, sometimes. Well they - they were there - for like the first half of the - year, and then - your next - the shooting was like after that - to - have company - for - for - in - from - company - they wer
e
 at - really - gentry you know I mean to say - they just like took the shooting, for the shooting season, and they had their friends - Hep Hepburn was the name of the - the gentleman, and - and - and - he brought his - brought his staff with him, had his 
- still with him, aye, staff with him. You see, they - they - we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Did they have lots of parties there of visitors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 We - that way - for the shooting season, and - and any - the - the - they had - friends from - Pitlochry too, who - they - the Hig
gins, Higgins' - I think it was Higgins they called the - the - from Pitlochry. And - and - or - they were awful kind to - they were honestly awful kind to mother and liked them. And my father had his - had - had his sheep and - and things to attend to, b
ut - but you had - we had plenty of outhouses too you see, and he - and then - and then of course - there was a lot of cattle. There was a lot of cattle too you see that mother saw to as well. And - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 She helped with the cows did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 And - a
nd - helped - aye, young - young - young cattle out there some of them - some of them was milking and anyway she did all the cows, their own cows - like - we'd always about two cows you see, so that you would - milk - milk the whole year round in that way
,
 and she kept two pigs. They were away - they were away from the - the sten, aw-a down I can mind - they were away down a good bit - for the sten you see. The sten - and - and - they'd two pigs and she - they - they - aye, they did well with the pigs - gr
eat big pigs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 What about killing the pigs, did your mother have to do with that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Aye - there were - oh I - well, any time - you were - they kept the - the - the bladder and made - the - puddings, black puddings, and - and - and then white pu
ddings you know, the washing of the puddings she - was great - there was a spigot near where you could - where you could do that you see, plenty of water supply. So - it was - an then - in the - the - the - kept going with the - the bacon, with the bacon 
- some - some of them wanted the bacon you see, to take - take bits away with them you see, pieces of the pigs away with them, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 They would smoke them at home would they or cure them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Cure them you see. They - they - were - like - mother like
 and father. Father did the curing, there were a - there were a big - outhouse - for - where they could lay them in the salt and - and cure them that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 You didn't go short of food then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Never go short of food. It was a great place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Your mother must have worked very hard though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Oh she worked hard - she worked - she had - she had a hard life you know, she - she - she'd a good - she'd a good way earning, and - and she said, she said she would - a rough way of life and good - good food
 and - and - and good ways and and then there were - there were good ways you see, and - buying of things as well and taking her out in that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 The people from the big house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Mm. They were - they were awful kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 When did they move to Tinwald then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Oh that was after - that was after - after we had been up Crawick Glen. He was - he left - he was about three year at Lochur - Lochur and he went to a wee - went to a wee school - at - it was - it was a wee school that my sister and I went to
, and - and you had to go - over a - just a pathway, just a pathway, it was - what - it was a good bit to go you see, and you had to go - keep on this pathway, for there was a lot of adders about you know, on the ground, there was a lot of adders, so I - 
we kept - mother kept us in boots you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 You didn't get to go with your bare feet in the summertime then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 No, no, never run with our bare feet. Never went out with our bare feet, no. Just we had to. It was - always vexed when we left Lochur, '
cos my dad was find - finding hard to get away up - to - have three mile - three mile out of Sanquar it was, up Crawick Glen, Crawick Glen they called it, and way - oh it's a different Sanquhar nowadays I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 It's grown like everything else hasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Everything else. You see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 How old would you be when you went up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
I would be coming on for twelve I think. Ten - twelve. We went to Sanquar - I went to Sanquhar school - you see, it was Sanquhar school then it was - and then it 
was - it - it turned into a Sanquhar Academy now, yes, it is and - just on - on what you call Queensbury Square, near - near to the old - old church, used to be - the - the old church it was then. It was - it was a Mr. Woods that was the - great big stout
 minister that - was the minister then, but he - he used to come and see us up Crawick Glen you see, he got a - if he got a lift with one of the farmers, but - and - took him up and brought him back maybe, he was a big stout man, was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Not very keen on walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 He was awful kind too. So kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 How long did your people stay at Crawick Glen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Oh were there - I - eleven years, the - they had - you see - they - they - they - this - and my father - gave up Lochur you see - it - it was gettin
g too much for him you see to - but he wanted a - a different kind of heather you see, when - he - a different kind there, a sheep and that you see - of - there was - sheevites in some parts and - and black faces in the other, they were rather different -
 
in some kinds of sheep. So - he'd no bother in getting - getting this place up Crawick Glen - Carco - Carco was the name of the farm, Carco, its - and - and - and - we got - his - his - shepherd's house - was where - was - was - just sitting across - and 
- and - and it was looking down onto the roadway, it was doing the - the road that - we were three mile off Sanquar of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 You had to walk that three miles to and from the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Aye - aye - to the - school. We went to school. We - we'd com
pany you know with the - with the other - there - there was two shepherds on you see, there was young - one - house away further up the road, and - and they come down and went to the school - all go down the road together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 It would be all right in good weather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Aye, and - when you turned - and my sister - my sister left the school - before me because she was - she wanted to - to pick up the dressmaking, the dressmaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Was she older then you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 She was older, a year and nine month older
 than me. She died - she's - she - got married of course and she went away to Australia. See - see. So - so she died, I think her husband's still alive yet you see but it'll be - he'll be in hospital. Because he was a sort of invalid. Up - well three mile
 
off Sanquhar. To this - well - he - he was - the farmer was like newly married - and - he - see - so my father had - had to be the - head shepherd you see, oh the house was nae very good when - the - the house that he got to live in wasna a very good one.
 
And - and he come on now to my - the big house at Lochur, he - we took it badly you see, and - and of course he was - he wasnae pleased to - at getting a house in this state and - and he was - and he was disgusted so he turned it straight away. So - the -
 the \endash  Mr. Hunter says \endash 
 Mr. Hunter had got a good character about him for the - well, he says, don't leave us, he says, he says, don't leave us, he says, you see, I'm just new - I've just newly taken over this farm you see, the - the shepherd and - and tha
t, and - and - was depending - on an experienced, and - my father and that for the sheep - for - for the hills. Oh it was a good big hill, a good big travel but then he was a young man, a younger man then you see. And - so - see - see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 So he stayed eleven years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Aye, he put his - his - he had - he was just getting it up, the first - before had put the first year in, he said, oh you could stay in a place like this, he says. OH, he says, I'll get all the work done for you, he says, I'll get it all
 repaired. And - and - both inside and outside you see. And - and a new door on. Like at the house. Aye. Had a good doing - it's a good while doing you see. However they made it very - respectable in every way and - and - my father just sort of - got - go
t on well, and he - and he was there for eleven years after that. Just seemed to work in - in - in - aye -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 They must have hit it off with each other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Got off - got on fine, they got on fine, he was a - he was a good master, he was a good - maste
r, Mr. Hunter. He - he - and - so it was always - he - my father he came to you see for anything. Aye, he had a - father had been a shepherd so long you see. So - and then it was hard - it was hard - the grocers - the - the grocers came up with their - wi
th their carts you know, the - had - so many days of the week and - and then you - had to get - the only thing was - when we was at - a Lochur we was used to beets you see, you had peats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 For the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Aye, like - for the - we had to do cutting 
of peats and - when there was a big moss, and we had - we had to work with them and that was the fire for the - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Did you have to help to go and get the peats too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Used to help to kind of build them up you know to - when they were - drying a
nd - oh there's a lot of work in the peat work, that's why they made - put up iron fires, it was a big -
