ok it over was - was from Liver}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 pool, a - a Mr - a Mr Hepburn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Was he your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 No. He was the - he just took on - it was - Stubbs - Stubbs and Calnder was the ones that - that - that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 That owned it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Aye, they owned it like and they were let - my father's - boss you see, and then - the - the - there were a young herd in the house too, the - see mother had to work with them all you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 She had to look after the herd as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Aye, look after them all, in - and - the - it was a good way of living but it was a lot of work to do. But my mother - mother somehow seemed to have - strength to do it, I don't know, she steadied - and 
- and it was pigs you had to work with. Peats. And - and - in this big range - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Was it a big kitchen that you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 It was a good big kitchen, flag floor. And - and - and then you had the - the back door - the back door and then there were a
 side door, that - that - that you could use, that you could use, but you - and you had - and then - and then there's a front door. Of course we didnae use the front door when the gentry was there, but when you had - when there were none of them there, yo
u had the full use of the whole house. All the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Which did you like best, when the people were there or when you had the house to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Well - it was cheery while the people were there you see. We had a lot of them and they were very friendly and very kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 How did you have to call them, did you have to call them ever madam, that sort of thing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Oh - oh well - sir - well sir was the thing for some of them. Some of the gentry, they - were - pretty well of you see, they - they - t
he head maids - the head maids - they were - friend - connected with Mr - with Mr Hepburn and - and he had - the big - tobacco - firm you see, you know the - Hignet Tobacco. Well there were - I think there were two brothers that used t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11414884\charrsid5586003 o come - but it was for the shoo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 ting season that they came for you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Did they ever bring any children that you could play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 No. No they - no, they were - they - they had no small children like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 They were just grown ups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 There was - there w
as a - there was a daughter at - daughter, she was - brought with them - a granddaughter of Mr Hepburn's, and - and she was very fond of us and - and she used to - play about with us outside you know and - and - well - in among the hay and she - used to t
ell us stories of - one thing and another. She - she was a - she was - she was on holiday as well yours, and she said - there were always a - a basket of pears come on the scene, then we got some pears to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 You had a grand time then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Oh we'd plen - we were awful happy. They were - they were awfully good to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
What about a normal day when there was nobody else living in the house, who would get up first when there was just you and your family there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Oh - my mother would be doing the 
fire and that, and then the young herd helped her to because he was - he was good in the house the young fel - the young her - young shepherd, he was - he was - from a shepherds house too - right down in - at Dunscore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 And so he would be used to a house like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
And he did a lot to help - lots of bits of things to help. And - and then my father had to be up early for the hills you see, to see what was going on there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Did he go out into and around the hills in the morning and then at night again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
He - at morning - he had to see the - see if they were all right you see. And especially in the lambing time, you see, they - they were - he - he was on the go two or three times. And you see - finding his way around. And feeding the lambs if 
they were heeding any attention. That's somebody knocking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Did your father always come home for his dinner or did he sometimes take a piece with him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 He - he - I - he took his piece with him if he was going to be working lately or - but he - he
 - he mostly got his - dinner. If he didnae get home - mother aye made his dinner at night you see. Made the - good meal at night, aye. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Did you have a big breakfast in the morning, did you get a cooked breakfast?
