well - some of them were his brothers, some of his brothers or brother-in-laws or something - see, so right round about Cranshaws you see, and - and that he was - and oh they were lovely - lovely hills too, beautiful heather hills. And - and - I loved the
 
hills you know because - they - there were as much - much white heather growing as what there were purple. It was lovely. Aye. I - I - I got a big bunch picked and - and sent it home. 'Cos we had nae heather hills you see. It was grass up at Carco you see
. But it was - oh it was grand.
