arbour's you know, Parks car - with his sons, and he was coming out of the - this - along that road, and - and you see my - I was going down the - Tinwald Brae on my bicycle, but still I was on the - on the right side that I should have been, right enough
 side that I should have been on, but I didnae know that - if he had been turning - turning the car down I would - I would have escaped all right. But you see he was turning right across the road to come up to Tinwald Brae you see, because -
