n 1945. And - so - oh he was a good big fine looking fellow, there were nae getting away from it. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 But you just hadn't thought about him at all as a husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 No, seriously like you see thinking that he'd do very well for a husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Was there anybody else that you thought you might like to marry before he came along?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
Oh there were a - odd ones that you - you know, that you - that you was work - working beside and that you know and - just be an odd time but - however - it didnae come off, it just had to be that fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
We've heard that in some places if there was a family came into the district that nobody liked, or if they had done something that people disapproved of, they used to go round to the house at night and make noises 
and bother the people 'til they went away. Have you heard of anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 
-No. No, there never - never - we never had any - you know, any difficulties, you know, in living in the country. In - in the cottages, my father and mother no - never any really disturbed us like that you see. But - they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Were there amny outsiders came to live round about you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Aye - aye, this - this farm - the - the - shepherds - shepherds you see, they had to come - and - and do the hammerings and things. Th
at was like when we was up Crawick Glen, aye. They - you see, they - they had - they come from far over the hills and that, and - and it was like what you call a handling day, you see, big day, and mother had to - mother had to feed them you see. She did 
-
 she - they were - they - generally done - it was generally done in - if the - at the folds as you call it, and the - and the stuff - the stuff was carted up to them, you know, the food - was - was carted up to them. Aye, just to save a - having - she had
nae room in the house for - see - had it outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Did you ever have any Irishmen coming over looking for work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Oh - oh there were - oh there were odd - odd Irishmen used to come round about. But - mother - mother never employed any of them. They
 never employed any of them like. Like the - that was round about. I don't know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Were they not keen on the Irish then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 No, don't think - you see, they - there - they were great workers of course you see a lot of them, but she - they didnae - yo
u see, father didnae - take on any - and then you see, Mr Hunter you see, it was just - newly taken on to this farm you see and - and - and he wasna employing anybody - that - very much either. See he was just starting you see. And his wife. So you see my
 
- and my father wanted to - to get away the first year, he says, oh he says, don't leave me here he says. Dinna leave, he said, because, he said, I've got such a good character about you, he says, and - and he says, I'm just starting this - this - this go
ing he says and - and to tell you the truth he says I know nothing about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 What sort offolk were they, were they the same sort of class as yourself or were they better off than your father would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 They - they what? They -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Were they the same sort of folk as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Yes. Yes. Oh they were - yes, the - they belonged to way about - Creetown - Creetown or something I think, aye, and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 They must have had a bit money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Aye, and - and - and they were both farming side you s
ee, but no the - it was the sheep I think - that - that - you see his was a sheep farm you see, and then my father was experienced in the she - in his sheep. So - he kept a hold of him, he says - he says, oh I want - I keep - keep a hold of you he says, d
inna go away and leave me now. So of course you see my father - my father - he says, I'll do all the repairs and things for you. Put all your stuff right, so - that settled things all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 I think you were quite happy up there weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 And 
- and we - eleven years we put in up there, and then - you see, mother - mother seemed to get the strength and she did all the inside work you know and - and then we'd a good way of - of living, because we could keep - we keep two cows, and two pigs, and 
a lot of hens, and all that see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9461452 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 Were you sort of told how many animals you could keep or was it must up to you yourselves to decide?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568274 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9263038\charrsid5586003 The - the - the - of course there - there were always - the cattle to look after in the byres you see. But that
 was how mother - they - they were away in the summertime you see.
\par }}